# Release process — IPBuilding Gateway

## Trigger

Apply when the user or task involves:

- `git tag v*.*.*`
- "nieuwe release", "tag een nieuwe versie", "bumper versie"
- Changing `version:` in `ipbuilding_gateway/config.yaml`

## Verplichte flow vóór `git tag`

1. Run `/codex-review` (skill: `BenedictKing/codex-review`) on uncommitted changes or the latest commit.
   - Confirm the generated CHANGELOG entry matches the intended change.
2. Update `ipbuilding_gateway/CHANGELOG.md` with the entry under the correct version section.
   - **Customer-facing taal.** Beschrijf wat de gebruiker merkt, niet hoe het werkt.
   - Gebruik de Keep-a-Changelog headers: `### Added`, `### Changed`, `### Fixed`, `### Removed`. Sla over wat niet van toepassing is.
   - Korte, leesbare bullets. Geen bestandsnamen, functienamen, commit-hashes, regelnummers, test-technische details, of interne implementatie-termen (tenzij de gebruiker die zelf zal zien).
   - Technische details horen in de commit message, niet in de CHANGELOG.
3. Bump `version:` in `ipbuilding_gateway/config.yaml` (semver; pre-1.0 uses `0.x.y`).
4. Commit: `release: v<X>.<Y>.<Z>` (conventional commit).
5. Tag: `git tag v<X>.<Y>.<Z>` and `git push --tags`.
6. CI (tags only) builds and publishes to `ghcr.io`.

## Wat NIET

- Do not rely on push to `main` for builds — `builder.yaml` runs only on `v*.*.*` tags.
- Do not expect PR CI builds for the add-on image.

## Codex-review (lokaal, niet in CI)

The BenedictKing/codex-review skill is a local editor tool (Node + Codex CLI + OpenAI key), not suitable for GitHub Actions.

Install: `npx skills add https://github.com/BenedictKing/codex-review --skill codex-review`
